author: Ben Kochman
title: Firefighters fight big Queens fire in frigid temperatures
text:
Hundreds of firefighters respond to big-time Queens blaze in frigid temperatures Firefighters fight big Queens fire in frigid temperatures 7-alarm fire on Liberty ave. and 111th Street. in Queens. (Bruce Cotler/for New York Daily News) Sunday, March 5, 2017, 1:42 AM 
A fast-moving inferno tore through a row of buildings in Queens Saturday night. 
Hundreds of firefighters were called to the 7-alarm blaze in a swath of two-story buildings at 110-114 Liberty Ave. in Jamaica around 11 p.m., the FDNY said. 
Smoke eaters battled the frigid cold and flames and were still working to get the fire under control early Sunday morning. At least five stores were damaged by the blaze. (Bruce Cotler/for New York Daily News) 
At least five stores were damaged by the blaze. FDNY Commissioner Daniel Nigro was on the scene with dozens of Fire and EMS crews. One person was injured in the fire and taken to the hospital in stable condition, officials said. Join the Conversation:
